sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client Application
    participant Gateway as vllm-orchestrator-gateway<br/>8090/TCP HTTP plaintext
    participant Orchestrator as FMS Guardrails Orchestrator<br/>8085/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Detectors as Guardrails Detectors<br/>(PII, regex, etc.)
    participant vLLM as vLLM<br/>(LLM Inference)

    Note over Client,vLLM: Flow 1: Guardrailed Chat Completion (No Detection Triggered)

    Client->>Gateway: POST /{route}/v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP plaintext<br/>Authorization header (optional)
    Note over Gateway: Route lookup<br/>Inject detector config<br/>from GatewayConfig
    Gateway->>Orchestrator: POST /api/v2/chat/completions-detection<br/>HTTP/HTTPS (optional mTLS)<br/>Client cert + forwarded Authorization
    Orchestrator->>Detectors: Content analysis request<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    Detectors-->>Orchestrator: Detection results (empty)
    Orchestrator->>vLLM: LLM inference request<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    vLLM-->>Orchestrator: Generated text response
    Orchestrator-->>Gateway: Chat completion response<br/>(no detections)
    Note over Gateway: No detections found<br/>Pass through response
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTP 200 JSON Response<br/>Original completion

    Note over Client,vLLM: Flow 2: Detection Triggered (Fallback Response)

    Client->>Gateway: POST /pii/v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP plaintext<br/>Authorization header (optional)
    Note over Gateway: Route: pii<br/>Inject PII detector config
    Gateway->>Orchestrator: POST /api/v2/chat/completions-detection<br/>HTTP/HTTPS (optional mTLS)<br/>Detectors: [regex-lang-detector]
    Orchestrator->>Detectors: PII detection analysis
    Detectors-->>Orchestrator: Detection results (PII found)
    Orchestrator->>vLLM: LLM inference request
    vLLM-->>Orchestrator: Generated text (contains PII)
    Orchestrator-->>Gateway: Response with detections field populated
    Note over Gateway: Detections found!<br/>Replace choices with<br/>configured fallback_message
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTP 200 JSON Response<br/>Fallback message substituted
